    <description>The Infrared Spectrometer (IKS) on Vega 1 and Vega 2 were identical. The IKS was a three-channel system with two high-resolution spectral channels for the chemical analysis of the cometary metter, gas, and dust, and an image modulation channel for measuring the size of and thermal emission from the nucleus. The short-wavelength spectral channel covered the range 2.5 - 5 microns; the long wavelength spectral channel covered the range 6-12 microns; and the imaging channel covered the range 7-14 microns.</description>
